    <p style="font-size:30px">

        Amritsar, located in the northwestern Indian state of Punjab, is a city steeped in history, spirituality, and culture.
        Known as the spiritual and cultural capital of Sikhism, Amritsar is famous for its iconic Golden Temple and vibrant street life.
        <h4 style="text-align:left ;font-weight:bold">Golden Temple (Harmandir Sahib):</h4>
        
    <p style="font-size:20px;text-align:left">The Golden Temple is the holiest shrine in Sikhism and one of the most visited religious sites in the world.
        Admire the breathtaking architecture of the temple, with its golden domes, marble walls, and serene Sarovar (sacred pool).
        Experience the spiritual atmosphere as pilgrims from all over the world gather to pay their respects and partake in the langar (community kitchen) serving free meals to all visitors.
    </p>


    <h4 style="text-align:left ;font-weight:bold">Jallianwala Bagh: </h4>
    <p style="font-size:20px ;text-align:left">
        Visit Jallianwala Bagh, a memorial garden commemorating the tragic massacre of hundreds of unarmed civilians by British troops in 1919.
        Explore the memorial's pathways, preserved bullet marks, and the Martyrs' Well, which serves as a reminder of the sacrifices made during India's struggle for independence.
    </p>


    


    



    <h4 style="text-align:left;font-weight:bold">Shopping:</h4>
    <ul style="text-align:left ; font-size:20px">
        <li>
            Stroll through the bustling markets of Amritsar, including the lively bazaars of Hall Bazaar and Katra Jaimal Singh, offering a variety of goods such as handicrafts, textiles, and traditional Punjabi attire.
        </li>
        <li>
            Don't forget to shop for souvenirs such as phulkari embroidery, juttis (traditional Punjabi footwear), and Amritsari papad (crispy lentil wafers).
        </li>
    </ul>



    <h4 style="text-align:left;font-weight:bold">Cultural Heritage:</h4>
    <ul style="text-align:left ; font-size:20px">
        <li>
            Discover the rich cultural heritage of Punjab through traditional music, dance, and cuisine.
        </li>
        <li>
            Attend a vibrant Punjabi folk dance performance or enjoy live music performances featuring traditional instruments such as the dhol (drum) and tumbi (string instrument).
        </li>
        <li>
            Sample authentic Punjabi cuisine, including mouthwatering dishes such as Amritsari kulcha, makki di roti with sarson da saag, and lassi (yogurt drink).
        </li>
    </ul>

    

    

    <h4 style="text-align:left;font-weight:bold">Accomodations:</h4>
    <ul style="text-align:left ; font-size:20px">
        <li>
            Choose from a range of accommodation options in Amritsar, including luxury hotels, boutique guesthouses, and budget-friendly lodgings.
        </li>
        <li>
            Stay in the vicinity of the Golden Temple for easy access to this iconic landmark and immerse yourself in the spiritual atmosphere of the city.
        </li>
    </ul>


    



